.TH "tty_ldisc_open" 9 "tty_ldisc_open" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
tty_ldisc_open \- open a line discipline
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" tty_ldisc_open
.BI "(struct tty_struct *tty "  ","
.BI "struct tty_ldisc *ld "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "tty" 12
tty we are opening the ldisc on
.IP "ld" 12
discipline to open

A helper opening method. Also a convenient debugging and check
point.

Locking: always called with BTM already held.
